    <item>
      <title>Core Semiotic Universe</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/core-semiotic-universe/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/core-semiotic-universe/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;../index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interactive semioverse&lt;/a&gt; extends a &lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe/semiotic-universe.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic universe&lt;/a&gt; — a self-sustaining &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; system in which everything sayable is meaningful and everything meaningful is sayable. The base layer provides:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;a meaning domain &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; that is a complete &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/heyting-algebra/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting algebra&lt;/a&gt; (intuitionistic, because not every question about a &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s meaning resolves to yes or no),&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;a modal &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;j&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;j&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizing &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;a &lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe/terms/trace-comonad.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;trace comonad&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizing semiotic provenance — the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; chains that produced each meaning,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;definable operators interpreted into &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (the grammar of the sign system),&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;fragments (bounded interpretive contexts) and a composite &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathcal{S}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This layer ensures that all semantic work is closed under logic, &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation, and semiotic provenance before any handle-facing interaction is added.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Footprints, Delta, and Subtraction</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/footprints-delta-subtraction/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/footprints-delta-subtraction/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surfaces&lt;/a&gt; in place, we can define how a handle affects the meaning domain and how to compare or remove that influence. These three operations formalize the pragmatic dimension of &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/semiosis.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiosis&lt;/a&gt;: meanings have consequences (footprints), those consequences can be compared (delta), and influence can be disciplinedly removed (subtraction).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;footprint&#34;&gt;Footprint&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/footprint.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;footprint&lt;/a&gt; of a handle is the closure of its &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/handle-fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle fragment&lt;/a&gt; under the state&amp;rsquo;s operators — the total meaning the handle acquires through all its &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; encounters. As a physical footprint &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;indexes&lt;/a&gt; the passage of a body, the semiotic footprint indexes the passage of a handle through the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Handles and Interactions</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/handles-interactions/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/handles-interactions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;../index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interactive semioverse&lt;/a&gt; introduces handles as &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;indexical&lt;/a&gt; references and defines a calculus of interactions that generate semantic material — formalizing how &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; engage with what lies outside the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;handles&#34;&gt;Handles&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; is a persistent &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;indexical&lt;/a&gt; reference to a thing. It is not itself an element of the meaning domain &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;; it is an external pointer mapped into &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; by a seed function &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;η&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\eta&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. This formalizes Peirce&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;index&lt;/a&gt;: a &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; connected to its object by existential relation rather than convention or resemblance.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Semantic and Semiotic Context</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/semantic-semiotic-context/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/semantic-semiotic-context/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The interactive semioverse draws on both semantic and &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; traditions, specifically those that align with a relational ontology — where relations are prior to entities. The mathematical structures correspond to concepts in &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/schools/peircean-semiotics.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Peircean&lt;/a&gt; semiotics: indexicality, habit, unlimited semiosis, and the pragmatic maxim.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;semantics&#34;&gt;Semantics&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Heyting algebra &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; provides the semantic domain — a constructive logic of meanings. The implication &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⇒&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;a \Rightarrow b&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; captures constructive entailment; the modal closure &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;j&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;j&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizes &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation; the trace &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizes semiotic provenance. These are the semantic structures that the interactive layer operates on.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
